D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693c67eb04eda4732f2d7617%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESatterlee's%20warehouse%20is%20lined%20with%20more%20than%20130%203D%20printers.%3Cp%3EDylan%20Ethier%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETeen%20entrepreneur%20Michael%20Satterlee%20built%20a%20six-figure%20e-commerce%20business%20using%203D%20printing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20started%20with%20minimal%20funds%2C%20leveraging%20free%20tools%20and%20rapid%20prototyping%20to%20test%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESatterlee%20now%20operates%20over%20130%20printers%20and%20is%20transitioning%20to%20working%20with%20a%20manufacturer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Satterlee%20knows%20a%20thing%20or%20two%20about%20launching%20businesses%20on%20a%20shoestring%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20still%20in%20middle%20school%20when%20he%20started%20his%20first%20e-commerce%20company%2C%20which%20sold%20a%20sand%20repellent%20product%20he%20created%20using%20hand%20sanitizer%20and%20cornstarch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20any%20money%20at%20the%20time%2C%20so%20I%20used%20a%20free%20app%20like%20Google%20Sites%20instead%20of%20Shopify%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20my%20checkout%2C%20I%20had%20an%20Amazon%20Handmade%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2018-year-old%20entrepreneur%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20referring%20to%20Amazon's%20marketplace%20for%20handcrafted%20goods%20that%20waives%20the%20monthly%20selling%20fee%20for%20approved%20makers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20I%20had%20a%20free%20Amazon%20account%2C%20a%20free%20Google%20Sites%20account%2C%20and%20then%20my%20'buy%20button'%20was%20just%20a%20link%20to%20my%20Amazon%20store.%20That's%20how%20I%20started%20selling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20sand%20repellent%20company%20funded%20his%20next%20venture%20%E2%80%94%20a%20clog%20accessory%20company%20called%20Solefully%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Solefully%20funded%20his%20homerun%20business%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcruisecup.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECruise%20Cup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20sells%20a%20variety%20of%20products%2C%20including%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenager-built-six-figure-ecommerce-business-with-3d-printers-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eviral%20%26quot%3Btactical%20reload%20can%20holder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20November%202025%20alone%2C%20Satterlee%20generated%20%24300%2C000%20in%20sales%2C%20which%20Business%20Insider%20verified%20by%20reviewing%20a%20screenshot%20of%20his%20Shopify%20dashboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20teen%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20his%20childhood%20home%20outside%20Albany%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20is%20foregoing%20college%20to%20scale%20Cruise%20Cup%2C%20explained%20how%20to%20start%20selling%20products%20online%20with%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22michael%20satterlee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693c5bbb832e0ef1ead62655%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Satterlee%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20Cruise%20Cup%2C%20the%20company%20behind%20the%20viral%20tactical%20reload%20can%20holder.%3Cp%3EDylan%20Ethier%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Start%20prototyping%20with%20a%203D%20printer.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20core%20component%20of%20launching%20an%20e-commerce%20business%20is%20working%20with%20a%20supplier%20to%20bring%20a%20product%20to%20life%2C%20a%20process%20that%20can%20be%20time-consuming%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20manufacturer%20is%20overseas%2C%20and%20expensive%2C%20as%20there's%20typically%20a%20minimum%20order%20quantity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatterlee's%20work%20around%20was%20to%20create%20products%20using%20a%203D%20printer.%20He%20learned%20about%203D%20printing%20and%20CAD%20(computer-aided%20design)%20modeling%20in%20a%20class%20he%20took%20his%20freshman%20year%20of%20high%20school%2C%20and%20is%20adamant%20that%20anybody%20could%20start%20creating%20and%20testing%20products%20with%20one.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20get%20a%203D%20printer%20for%20like%20100%20bucks%2C%20and%20a%20roll%20of%20filament%20costs%20like%20%2420.%20They%20make%20the%20modeling%20software%20so%20easy%20now%3B%20there's%20even%20AI%20where%20you%20could%20just%20type%20in%20a%20prompt%2C%20and%20it%20will%20come%20up%20with%20a%20model%20for%20you%20that'll%20be%20ready%20to%203D%20print.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt'll%20take%20some%20tinkering%20before%20you%20have%20a%20product%20you're%20satisfied%20with%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20I%20come%20up%20with%20the%20idea%2C%20I%20get%20the%20CAD%2C%20and%20I%20start%20working%20on%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20pretty%20rare%20that%20I%20nail%20something%20first%20try.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he's%20able%20to%20move%20a%20lot%20quicker%20than%20if%20he%20were%20working%20with%20a%20manufacturer%2C%20sending%20samples%20back%20and%20forth.%20It%20took%20about%20three%20days%20of%20prototyping%20to%20get%20the%20first%20version%20of%20his%20viral%20can%20holder%20down%2C%20and%20about%20a%20week%20to%20get%20the%20product%20listed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20work%20with%20some%20people%20to%20get%20the%20website%20images%20up%20and%20get%20some%20animations%2C%20make%20the%20website%20look%20really%20nice%2C%20and%20then%20I%20would%20say%2C%20within%20a%20week%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20the%20product%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Test%20multiple%20product%20ideas.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESatterlee%20believes%20in%20creating%20a%20product%20quickly%20and%20iterating%20from%20there%2C%20rather%20than%20spending%20months%20trying%20to%20perfect%20it.%20That's%20a%20major%20advantage%20of%20working%20with%20a%203D%20printer%3A%20you%20can%20create%20products%20within%20days%20and%20at%20a%20low%20cost%2C%20and%20then%20test%20the%20market%20before%20deciding%20to%20invest%20time%2C%20money%2C%20and%20materials%20in%20producing%20something%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolefully%20came%20about%20after%20he%20experimented%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20products%20on%20Etsy%20before%20one%20took%20off%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsolefully.com%2Fproducts%2Fsnow-plow-attachment-for-crocs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20snowplow%20attachment%20for%20clogs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20seeing%20the%20demand%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20build%20an%20entire%20store%20around%20clog%20accessories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20make%20whatever%20idea%20you%20have%20exist%20first%2C%20and%20then%20make%20it%20good%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20would%20tell%20me%20all%20the%20time%2C%20'What's%20the%20point%20of%20a%20can%20cooler%20if%20it's%203D%20printed%3F%20It's%20not%20insulated.%20It's%20not%20going%20to%20keep%20the%20drink%20cold.'%20But%20I%20didn't%20care.%20I%20had%20the%20vision.%20If%20you%20have%20an%20idea%2C%20just%20bring%20it%20to%20life%20as%20fast%20as%20you%20can%2C%20and%20then%20go%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Take%20advantage%20of%20low-cost%20and%20free%20resources.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20e-commerce%20space%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20the%20startup%20costs%20are%20free%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Satterlee.%20Once%20you%20have%20the%20essential%20supplies%20%E2%80%94%20a%20printer%20and%20filament%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20start%20creating%20and%20posting%20content%20on%20social%20media%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstagram%20and%20TikTok%20are%20the%20biggest%20things%20when%20you're%20starting%20out%20because%20you%20want%20to%20get%20a%20following%20and%20you%20want%20to%20get%20organic%20sales%20and%20organic%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Rather%20than%20buying%20ads%2C%20he%20focused%20on%20creating%20viral%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20your%20selling%20platform%2C%20%